name: Spacious apartment close to centre town - WI-FI
description:
Tranquil apartment situated in S'Agaro with restricted side sea views from balcony.

My place is indicated specially for nature lovers as the apartment is next to 'Cami de Ronda' the walkway where you can admire the beauty of the Costa Brava (see pictures).

Easy walking access to the beaches of Sant Pol (10 minutes), Sant Feliu (15 minutes) and 'La Conca' (20 minutes), times depending on fitness and route.
There is a map in the apartment providing shortcuts to move around Sant Feliu.
neighborhood_overview: The area is full of second residence owners from Barcelona and abroad. Busy on summer times and weekends and tranquil the rest of the year.
host_about: I have lived in the UK for over a decade and now travelling a lot due to work. In my home town in Spain I miss the most the sun light. I love walking along 'Cami de Ronda' (coastal walkaway) every day when I am in S'Agaro and feel the sea breeze coming from the bay with it's salty smell. When visiting I prefer to leave the car parked and walk everywhere. Black coffee is very important to me first thing in the morning and dark chocolate (up to 80% cocoa) is my favourite treat. On my past trips I have had great times relaxing in Santorini, walking New York city from Bronx to Brooklyn, hiking Iceland landscapes, discovered hidden museums in Bruges, enjoying spa and beaches in Menorca, I dance on Bilbao's BBK festival, I keep enjoying the company of my good friend Oihana in San Sebastian, also I am discovering Zug and the landscapes in Switzerland and I had lots of fun dancing and drinking guinness in Dublin to mention one of the few places I have visited.

name: 70's Beach villa with garden,  beach at 400m.
description:
This beautiful, fun house was designed in 1971 by Joan Bosch. It has a big, relaxing garden, with some fruit trees and patios that are great for relaxing and dining in the summery evenings.
Great location, a couple minutes walk to the beautiful beach of Sant MartÃ­ and its medieval town.
l'Escala is also a short ride away.
We've loved this place for many years - we're confident you will too!
+ Surprising house
+ 3 min. to beach
+ Peaceful area
- Parts of the house need renovation
neighborhood_overview:
St Marti d'Empuries and L'Escala are 2 old fishing villages that have not yet been discovered by mass tourism. Both villages are within walking distance of the house and offer some beautiful quiet beaches.
St. MartÃ­ d'EmpÃºries is a very small, scenic village that has only a couple of streets, a medieval church and a small square with a couple of restaurants, atop of a hill overlooking the beach.
By riding a bycicle along the beach promenade, it takes 10 minutes to reach L'Escala, a bigger town with a good range of shops and conveniences.

The beach is at a 3 minute walk from the house. The beach is quiet and there is fine sand. On the beach there is a small bar for a snack and a drink. In the evenings there often is live music played by local musicians.
Within 3 minutes you walk up the village square of the small village of St Marti d'Empuries; a small square with cozy terraces. Ideal for eating or drinking a snack close to home in the evening.

Pals is a charming medieval village located in the picturesque Costa Brava region of Catalonia, Spain. With its cobblestone streets, centuries-old stone houses and panoramic views of green fields and the Mediterranean Sea, Pals will transport you back to medieval times as you revel in its authentic atmosphere and rich history. Let yourself be seduced by its charming corners, delicious local dishes and cozy atmosphere - a unique experience not to be missed during your visit to the Costa Brava!
In addition, the beach of Pals offers you a unique combination of golden sand, crystal clear waters and an incomparable natural environment. Surrounded by beautiful cliffs and lush Mediterranean vegetation, this beach is the perfect place to relax, enjoy the sun and take a refreshing dip in the sea. With its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Pals beach is a must-see destination for beach lovers looking to escape the hustle and bustle and connect with nature in an idyllic setting.

name: Casa familiar decimonÃ³nica con mucho encanto
description:
Beautiful and rustic renovated family house from the early 1900s located in the center of Sant Feliu de Guixols. It is a welcoming royal estate, representative of the Catalan nineteenth-century style and preserves its original architectural values.
Perfect for 8 people. It is distributed on two floors, with 1 double bedroom and a bathroom on the ground floor and 3 double bedrooms and a bathroom with bathtub on the first floor. As a private outdoor part it has a magnificent garden patio and a terrace.
neighborhood_overview: Sant Feliu de GuÃ­xols is a municipality that belongs to the Baix EmpordÃ  Region, traditionally considered the capital of the Costa Brava. It is an important tourist and marine town, with an important mountainous and forest part, at the foot of the Massif de l 'Ardenya-Cadiretes, with countless trails and fantastic coves and views from the peaks and the cliffs over the sea.    Historically, the main activity was the cork industry, along with fishing, but from the 1950s, tourism became the main driver. It has several places and centers of landscape, architectural and cultural interest, including Pedralta, the Hermitage of Sant Elm, the famous Porta Ferrada International Festival, which this year will have its 59 edition or the Monastery with the famous Porta Ferrada, where for a few years there is the Espai Carmen Thyssen, intended to show the personal collection of the Baronian which is materialized in an ongoing programming of temporary exhibitions.

name: Sant Antoni de Calonge-Costa Brava
description:
Amazing! The apartment is equipped with the maximum possible benefits, we know that you want enjoy your holiday or your stay in Sant Antoni de Calonge, with the whole family and that is why we want to make it easy for you. You will rest in a large bed, you can relax enjoying a nap in front of the large window, a good swim in the pool or a long day on the beach.
Would you like to visit the central part of the Costa Brava on foot? From our apartment it is possible!
neighborhood_overview:
We are in the middle of the village of Sant Antoni de Calonge, 200m from the main beach. Here you will feel at home. The town has a lot of services and activities for couples, families and groups. You cannot miss activities of all kinds, as well as games and water parks, cinemas, shops, cultural activities such as the fishing museum, magnificent trekking or trekking routes, scuba diving, sailing, windsurfing, horse riding, tennis and many more activities Our magnificent local cuisine of meat, fish and seafood you have to try!
Our privileged location allows you to make trips to other places in the region, as well as the Costa Brava and the Gavarres mountains and reach the city of Girona. Enjoy golf courses, mountain bike circuits, trekking, horse riding, are other activities that you can do around us to enjoy your stay.

description:
It is a refuge of wellness and tranquility with a garden 5 minutes from the forest. Comfortable for long stays and teleworking 2 people.

The quiet promenade of Font Vella with almost centuries-old chestnut trees connects the town with the renowned spring of Font Vella. A few steps from local commerce establishments with km0 products: pastry, butchery, bakery, pond, grocery store and 5 minutes from the bus station that connects the town with the world.

At the end of the walk is the Balneari de la Font Vella, nice to see the building or even enjoy some of its health and relaxation treatments.

From Casa Venturita you can access in a few minutes the most basic routes, the Font del Pic or the Font Vella accessible and comfortable to enjoy the magnificent natural environment.

neighborhood_overview:
Pals is a charming medieval village located in the picturesque Costa Brava region of Catalonia, Spain. With its cobblestone streets, centuries-old stone houses and panoramic views of green fields and the Mediterranean Sea, Pals will transport you back to medieval times as you revel in its authentic atmosphere and rich history. Let yourself be seduced by its charming corners, delicious local dishes and cozy atmosphere - a unique experience not to be missed during your visit to the Costa Brava!
In addition, the beach of Pals offers you a unique combination of golden sand, crystal clear waters and an incomparable natural environment. Surrounded by beautiful cliffs and lush Mediterranean vegetation, this beach is the perfect place to relax, enjoy the sun and take a refreshing dip in the sea. With its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Pals beach is a must-see destination for beach lovers looking to escape the hustle and bustle and connect with nature in an idyllic setting.

description: Get ready to live the experience of your dreams in this spectacular 80m2 apartment in the golf area of Pals! With a 100m2 terrace that will take your breath away and only a short 15 minute walk to the paradisiacal beach of Pals, this place is simply irresistible.
neighborhood_overview:
Pals is a charming medieval village located in the picturesque Costa Brava region of Catalonia, Spain. With its cobblestone streets, centuries-old stone houses and panoramic views of green fields and the Mediterranean Sea, Pals will transport you back to medieval times as you revel in its authentic atmosphere and rich history. Let yourself be seduced by its charming corners, delicious local dishes and cozy atmosphere - a unique experience not to be missed during your visit to the Costa Brava!
In addition, the beach of Pals offers you a unique combination of golden sand, crystal clear waters and an incomparable natural environment. Surrounded by beautiful cliffs and lush Mediterranean vegetation, this beach is the perfect place to relax, enjoy the sun and take a refreshing dip in the sea. With its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Pals beach is a must-see destination for beach lovers looking to escape the hustle and bustle and connect with nature in an idyllic setting.

neighborhood_overview:
Ampuriabrava, located on the Costa Brava of Spain, is known as the "Venice of the Costa Brava" due to its system of navigable canals. It's a coastal destination that combines the beauty of its golden sand beaches and crystal clear waters with the convenience of being able to dock boats directly at the properties, which attracts lovers of boating and water sports. The city has a varied offer of restaurants, bars and shops as well as a lively tourist atmosphere.

In addition to boating, Ampuriabrava offers opportunities for outdoor activities such as cycling, hiking, water sports. The town also hosts festivals and events throughout the year, making it an attractive destination during all seasons. Its mix of canals, beach and entertainment make it a unique place on the Catalan coast to enjoy a vacation full of fun and scenic beauty.

name: Date el placer de sentirte como en casa
description:
Welcome to our apartment in Girona! If you're looking for a place to feel at home, it's your vacation home. Effortlessly and within walking distance you can walk around the old town. And for cycling lovers, we are right at the crossroads of both road and mountain biking trails.
If you arrive on AVE, on foot, by bus or taxi, you arrive at your apartment in a few minutes. Comfortable parking, free right outside your door. Book now, we guarantee you'll have an unforgettable experience!
neighborhood_overview:
Apartment located at the edge of the Old Quarter of Girona, also known as the Casco Antiguo, is a medieval area located at the heart of the city of Girona in the region of Catalonia. It is one of the most important and best preserved historical sites in all of Europe.
The Barri Vell is surrounded by a medieval wall that dates back to the 9th century, and inside it houses a maze of narrow, cobblestone streets that invite you to get lost and discover its charms. The architecture of the area is a mix of styles ranging from Romanesque, Gothic, Renaissance to Baroque, which makes strolling through its streets like traveling through time.
One of the main attractions of the Old Quarter is the Cathedral of Girona. It is an imposing Gothic building with a surprising facade and a main nave of great beauty. In addition, inside the Cathedral is the Museo de Arte de Girona, where you can admire works of medieval and Renaissance art.

name: Casamar - Pals
description: Immerse yourself in the appeal of this incredible 145mÂ² house, located in the paradisiacal setting of Playa de Pals. Just 600 meters from the beach and surrounded by a wide variety of services, this location has everything you need to enjoy to the fullest!
neighborhood_overview:
Pals is a charming medieval village located in the picturesque Costa Brava region of Catalonia, Spain. With its cobblestone streets, centuries-old stone houses and panoramic views of green fields and the Mediterranean Sea, Pals will transport you back to medieval times as you revel in its authentic atmosphere and rich history. Let yourself be seduced by its charming corners, delicious local dishes and cozy atmosphere - a unique experience not to be missed during your visit to the Costa Brava!
In addition, the beach of Pals offers you a unique combination of golden sand, crystal clear waters and an incomparable natural environment. Surrounded by beautiful cliffs and lush Mediterranean vegetation, this beach is the perfect place to relax, enjoy the sun and take a refreshing dip in the sea. With its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Pals beach is a must-see destination for beach lovers looking to escape the hustle and bustle and connect with nature in an idyllic setting.
